## 2. Service-level deep dive

## 2.1 Ingestion service (Port 8001)

### 2.1.1 API endpoints

- `GET /health`
- `POST /documents`
- `GET /documents/{document_id}`
- `GET /documents/{document_id}/sections`
- `GET /metrics`

### 2.1.2 Upload handling modes

`POST /documents` supports:

1. **Multipart** (`file` key)
2. **Raw PDF body** with `Content-Type: application/pdf` or `application/octet-stream`, optional `X-Filename`

Validation rules:

- Reject if no file-like payload
- Reject non-`.pdf` extension
- Store file to configured uploads directory

Metrics incremented:

- `documents_upload_total`
- `documents_parsed_total`
- `documents_parse_failed_total`
- `document_parse_duration_seconds`

Failure path:

- Persist `Document(status="failed", error_message=...)`
- Return HTTP 422

### 2.1.3 Parsing strategy (parser.py)

Core parser behavior:

- Uses PyMuPDF (`fitz`) text extraction page-by-page.
- Cleans lines and drops noise:
  - page markers,
  - file paths,
  - punctuation-only lines,
  - tiny fragments.
- Splits inline numeric headings and heading-body composites (`1.2 Something ...`).
- Identifies headings via regex heuristics:
  - section headings,
  - subsection headings,
  - numeric-only subsections,
  - title-case all-caps heading pattern.
- Detects repeated boilerplate (headers/footers) across pages and strips them.
- Preserves opening preamble block semantics when detected.
- Splits embedded numbered subheadings in body text.
- Prevents over-fragmentation by keeping numeric-only child nodes inside a top-level parent where appropriate.
- Tracks `page_start`/`page_end` per section.
- Fallback: if no sections are found, emits one `Document Body` section with full text.

### 2.1.4 Ingestion persistence model

`Document`:

- `id`, `title`, `filename`, `status`, `error_message`, `created_at`

`Section`:

- `id`, `document_id`, `section_order`, `section_title`, `content`, `page_start`, `page_end`

