## 4. End-to-end audit lifecycle: exact control flow

## 4.1 `POST /audits` entry

1. Persist `Audit(status="pending")`.
2. Invoke `run_audit(db, audit)` synchronously.
3. On exception: rollback and mark audit `failed`.

## 4.2 `run_audit` initialization

At start:

- Mark audit as `running`.
- Persist model and corpus metadata from config.
- Pull all sections from ingestion service.
- Initialize metrics and budget state.

Computed global artifacts before looping sections:

- `cross_references = _extract_notice_cross_references(sections)`
- `(source_scope, source_scope_confidence, unseen_sections) = _source_scope_qualification(...)`
- scope proof gate downshift if proof insufficient
- `document_mode = _infer_document_mode(sections)` (privacy_notice vs internal_policy)
- `posture = _document_posture_agent(...)`
- `duty_validation = _document_wide_duty_validation(...)`
- `obligation_map = _build_document_obligation_map(...)`
- `llm_budget_cap = _effective_llm_budget(...)`

## 4.3 Per-section loop (dense breakdown)

For each section (ordered):

### A. Runtime guardrails

- hard runtime budget check (`MAX_AUDIT_RUNTIME_SECONDS`) → immediate `needs review` fallback finding if exceeded.

### B. Applicability filter layer

- `_is_not_applicable(section)` gate for obvious non-auditable content.
- `_section_auditability_type(section)` to classify definition/admin/meta sections.
- filtered sections persist as not-applicable support artifacts.

### C. Issue spotting layer

- `_collection_mode(section)` (direct/indirect/mixed/etc)
- `_spot_candidate_issues(section, collection_mode)` emits ranked candidate issue objects with evidence signal strengths.
- if document-level duty validation indicates unmet obligations, inject candidate issue at head (obligation-first enforcement).
- suppress controller-missing candidates if global obligation map confirms controller identity/contact already present.

### D. Legal qualification layer

- Extract legal facts (`_extract_legal_facts`) from section text.
- Compute legal qualification (`_legal_qualification_for_issue`) containing:
  - issue_name
  - obligation_family
  - defect_type
  - priority_bucket (material/fatal)
  - primary article
  - secondary articles
  - rejected articles
  - fit/rejection rationale

### E. Retrieval/RAG layer

- Build retrieval query via:
  `"GDPR obligations for {topic}. Context: {article_hint}. Section text: {snippet}"`
- Query knowledge service with `k=8`.
- Rerank based on document mode + section topic + article preferences.
- Keep top 5.
- Retry if low score or weak keyword overlap.

### F. Evidence sufficiency gate

- Must have at least 2 strong chunks (`score >= 0.50`) and at least one chunk containing obligation words.
- If insufficient:
  - for core privacy-notice duties, may produce a substantive probable partial gap from deterministic silence inference;
  - otherwise force `needs review`.

### G. LLM invocation gate

- If previous rate-limited or llm budget exhausted: deterministic `needs review` finding.
- Else call `run_llm_classification(...)` with section, chunks, and section guidance.

### H. LLM post-processing

- Coerce JSON to `LlmFinding` schema.
- sanitize legal references in notes.
- demote if model emits `candidate_publishability=internal_only`.
- demote if finding appears to be internal control only (privacy notice context mismatch).

### I. Applicability + specialized legal passes

- Infer claim types from finding text and fallback to section signals.
- Build applicability memo and applicability decision.
- Trigger specialized family passes (profiling, transfer, role ambiguity, special category).

### J. Citation validation / salvage

- Validate LLM citations against retrieved top-k set and allowed article matrix.
- Check paragraph compatibility.
- salvage citations from retrieved pool if needed.

### K. Deterministic violation and consistency overrides

- explicit violation library can force status to high-severity gap.
- normalize severity by claim type and risk tier.
- enforce reasoning-chain quality.
- append applicability and legal qualification traces in gap note for internal pathing.
- global consistency validator can demote to needs-review internal-only artifacts.
- not-assessable disallowed under explicit factual signal conditions.

### L. Duplicate suppression

- Signature-based dedupe across sections (`_finding_signature`).
- duplicates converted into diagnostic internal-only artifacts.

### M. Persist section finding

Persist `Finding` with:

- final status/classification
- confidence decomposition
- scope and omission flags
- legal fields and reasoning text
- publish flag pre-projection

Persist `FindingCitation` rows for validated citations.

### N. Optional split finding

- If combined controller/contact + legal basis context appears in one finding, creates second split legal-basis finding with dedicated legal anchors.

## 4.4 Post-loop synthesis and publication pipeline

After all sections:

1. `_add_notice_level_synthesis` (when privacy_notice)
2. `_add_systemic_issue_synthesis`
3. `_build_systemic_support` (anchors, support completeness, omission basis, source scope)
4. `_enforce_core_and_specialist_completeness`
5. `_build_final_disposition_map`
6. `_final_publication_validator`
7. `_enforce_review_publish_invariant`
8. `_record_suppression_ledger(... final_disposition_map snapshot ... )`
9. `_partner_review_pass`
10. `_upsert_evidence_records`
11. `_state_invariant_validator`
12. `_snapshot_analysis_items`
13. Set audit `complete`, set `completed_at`

