## 5. LLM subsystem details (exact prompting and provider strategy)

## 5.1 System prompt contract

The system prompt requires strict JSON keys:

- `status`, `severity`, `gap_note`, `remediation_note`, `policy_evidence_excerpt`, `legal_requirement`, `gap_reasoning`, `confidence_level`, `assessment_type`, `severity_rationale`, `citations`, `candidate_publishability`

Rules include:

- allowed statuses: compliant/partial/gap/needs review
- cite only provided chunks (`chunk_id + article_number`)
- partial/gap requires concrete citation
- if weak evidence → needs review
- privacy notices: prioritize Articles 12-14
- avoid certain governance articles as primary disclosure anchors
- transfer-specific citation guidance constraints

## 5.2 User prompt construction

Prompt includes:

- section title
- section content (up to 5000 chars)
- all retrieval chunk lines with metadata and snippet
- section-specific legal guidance string from deterministic guidance rules
- frozen rubric directives and citation constraints

## 5.3 Provider routing and fallback

`run_llm_classification` tries provider chain:

- primary provider from env (`MODEL_PROVIDER`)
- fallback provider from env (`FALLBACK_MODEL_PROVIDER`)

Provider adapters:

- Groq via OpenAI-compatible `/chat/completions` with JSON response format.
- Gemini via `generateContent` with `responseMimeType: application/json`.

429 handling:

- retries with bounded sleep,
- surfaces sentinel `__rate_limited__` if all attempts rate-limited.

