## 9. API projection layers (`/findings`, `/analysis`, `/review`)

## 9.1 `/findings` (published boundary)

- blocks entirely when audit is `review_required`.
- sources rows from canonical exported dataset function.
- derives issue key/label and sanitizes all user-facing fields.
- enforces evidence linkage against `EvidenceRecord` map.
- filters synthetic/systemic-anchor citations out of public projection.
- maps classification/status into external view fields.

## 9.2 `/analysis`

- exposes internal analysis candidates with optional filters.
- can suppress ledger rows unless debug mode.

## 9.3 `/review`

- merges publishable findings + blocked/internal findings + selected analysis rows.
- synthesizes review blocks from final disposition snapshot ledger row.
- grouped endpoint partitions into publication blockers, core duty resolution, specialist resolution, publishable, internal unresolved, diagnostics.

## 9.4 `/final-decision-ledger`

- outputs canonical issue keys and scope-level ledger rows with evidence refs and visibility flags.

